            <div type="translation" resp="part:emfr">
                
                <p n="1">
                    Prosperity! Fortune!
                </p>
                <p>...</p>
                
                <p n="209">
                    I, Karuṇākara Ācārya, alias Saṅkara Kāṭāṭi, master carpenter residing in Kuvaḷālam<note>That is, Kōlār, in Karnataka.</note> in Kuvaḷālanāṭu, I have engraved the letters of this order while <supplied reason="subaudible">the king</supplied> graciously uttered <supplied reason="subaudible">it</supplied> with his glorious mouth.
                </p>
                <p n="210">
                    Do not forget virtue/<foreign>dharma</foreign> <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>aṟam</foreign></supplied>. Other than virtue/<foreign>dharma</foreign> <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>aṟam</foreign></supplied>, there is no refuge/help/support <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tuṇai</foreign></supplied>.
                </p>
                
                <p n="211">
                    Sentient beings should protect <supplied reason="subaudible">this donation</supplied>!
                </p>
                
            </div>
            
